P3.18 FIXED - Config Error Logging

## Problem
config.go:36 silently ignored config file load errors with '_ = err'
Comment said 'log but don't fail' but NO LOGGING existed

## Solution
Added proper warning logging for config file parse errors:

1. Added imports:
   - log/slog
   - github.com/cjmartian/agent-deploy/internal/logging

2. Changed error handling:
   - Missing config file is expected behavior, not logged
   - Uses logging.ComponentSpending for consistent tagging
   - Logs reason (err.Error()) for debugging

## Test Output
TestLoadLimits_InvalidConfigFile now shows:
'WARN could not load config file, using defaults component=spending reason=parse config: invalid character...'

## Why This Matters
- Operators can now see when config file has syntax errors
- Helps debug misconfiguration issues
- Silent failures no longer hide problems
